## [2026-03-07] session-1
**Decision**: Use claude-sonnet-4-6 for debate turns, claude-haiku-4-5-20251001 for summaries
**Why**: Sonnet for quality debate reasoning; Haiku for cheap rolling summaries between rounds
**Alternatives rejected**: All-Sonnet (too expensive for summaries), all-Haiku (quality too low for debate)
---

## [2026-03-07] session-1
**Decision**: Start with Phase 1 spec implementation only (no Phase 2 features)
**Why**: Get working v1 first; Phase 2 (Annals, Forge, Barracks, Tribune) is out of scope for v1 per spec
**Alternatives rejected**: Building Phase 2 alongside (too much scope creep)
---

## [2026-03-07] session-1
**Decision**: Use Anthropic.SDK NuGet package (official) for Claude API calls
**Why**: Official SDK, well-maintained, supports streaming
**Alternatives rejected**: Raw HttpClient (more work, less reliable)
---

## [2026-03-07] session-1 (continued after context compaction)
**Decision**: Use `new Message(RoleType.User, text)` constructor + `response.Message.ToString()` for Anthropic.SDK 5.x
**Why**: SDK 5.x changed API — TextBlock type removed, Message constructor takes string directly
**Alternatives rejected**: TextBlock (not in SDK 5.x), anonymous object initializer (wrong overload)
---

## [2026-03-07] session-1
**Decision**: Create shared `GladiatorVm` record in `Colosseum.Web/Components/UI/Models.cs`
**Why**: GladiatorStrip and Arena.razor both needed the same view model type; separate definitions caused type mismatch
**Alternatives rejected**: Defining in each file (duplicate type error), using Core Gladiator model directly (ties UI to domain)
---

## [2026-03-07] session-1
**Decision**: Use `.slnx` solution format (not `.sln`)
**Why**: .NET 10 `dotnet new sln` creates `.slnx` by default; `.sln` is legacy format
**Alternatives rejected**: `.sln` (old format, not default in .NET 10)
---
